I've hit weight loss plateau, stuck on weight since June having the same routine of weight loss workouts and balanced diet but still not losing! How to break this plateau??
Chloe Marcellino Thankyou so much.

Sounds crazy but maybe give yourself I bit of time off from working out so much. It could just be a couple of days but you will give your body time to rest. When you are fatigued your actual exertion is a lot lower than you think. Also maybe switch up your routine. If you are doing lots of cardio maybe incorporate more residence and strength training. It burns just as much fat and calories but helps to build muscle which boost metabolism and weight loss. Also you could have hit a plateau if you are strength training as you are now putting on muscle which weighs more than fat. I hope this helps you
